title: Star-Spangled Banner National Historic Trail: Partners
body: Partners       National historic trails are partnership endeavors, spanning vast distances and involving many different jurisdictions. The Star-Spangled Banner Trail already involves numerous partners with whom the NPS is working to develop and sustain the Trail. The Advisory Council for the Star-Spangled Banner Trail consists of representatives of federal and state agencies and Chesapeake Bay related organizations. The council assists the National Park Service in development and implementation, identifying significant trail resources, and other matters.
